              <h3 class="question">Can I pre-book a Woodland Room?</h3>
              <p>It is not possible to book a room in advance of the birth because your clinical condition and that of your baby will need to be assessed before a decision is made as to your suitability to be in a self-contained room. However, once your suitability has been assessed please ask your midwife if there is a room available for you to use.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="">
              <h3 class="question">How will my birth experience impact on my suitability for a Woodland Room?</h3>
              <p>If you give birth by caesarean section or have experienced any complications either prior to, during, or following the birth of your baby you will need to be cared for in the ward area. This will also include if your baby requires any specific treatment or observations. Ask your midwife about your suitability to use a Woodland Room when you have given birth.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
